        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#smith-porcher1864"/>, p. 113, n. <citedRange>14</citedRange> and pl. 81</bibl> (whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SGDI"/> <citedRange>4841</citedRange></bibl>); 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>31</citedRange>, fig. 29</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>009200</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65919"><name nymRef="#Φιλῖνος"><supplied reason="undefined" evidence="previouseditor">Φι</supplied>λῖνος</name> 
                        <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65920"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Φιλῖνος">Φιλίνου</name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><rs type="office" key="eponymous priest"><w lemma="ἱαριτεύω">ἱαριτεύων</w></rs>
                    <lb n="3"/><w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀνέθηκε</w>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:id="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Philinos fils de Philinos a consacré durant sa prêtrise.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:id="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Philinos son of Philinos dedicated while being priest.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:id="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Philinos figlio di Philinos ha dedicato durante il suo sacerdozio.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>أهداها فيلينوس بن فيلينوس عندما كان كاهناً.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Although not further mentioned, this priest was the eponymous priest of Apollo. His name is given with the koine instead of the predictable dialectal form.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
